Class Summary
Class Description
BigCat
public class means it is available to all other classes and can create a BigCat Object in all other classes.
Cat
Abstract class Cat means you can't create an instance of this class, you can have an abstract reference to concrete subclass of Cat, such as Lion.
CatAdmirer
A class can be blank and does not need to have any code in it To see video tutorial for this section of code Video tutorial For all 177 videos, which cover all the topics in this course go to Complete Course Video Tutorial
Lion
this class is a subclass of abstract class Cat and has to provide a body for the abstract method Cat.clean() As any class that is a sub class of a abstract super class has to override the abstract methods of the super class
Lynx
This is a concrete sub class of a concrete super class BigCat and will only have access to the public and protected variables of this class which are the public variable BigCat.name and the protected variable BigCat.hasFur.
